+- [x] [Review][Patch] Inadequate Test Masking ÔÇö `MockEnv` returns all `True` for legal actions, skipping tests for MCTS masking logic.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] UnboundLocalError at Root ÔÇö In MCTS, if all legal actions are false at root, `done` is referenced before assignment.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] Pure Python List in Legal Actions ÔÇö `env.get_legal_actions()` returns a list instead of a NumPy array, risking element-wise failures.
+- [x] [Review][Defer] Security Vulnerability in Pickle ÔÇö `pickle.load()` is insecure (deferred, pre-existing prototype tool).
+- [x] [Review][Defer] Synchronous Agent Forward in MCTS ÔÇö `agent.forward` is called synchronously in the simulation loop, an anti-pattern (deferred, pre-existing architectural choice).
+- [x] [Review][Defer] Flawed Zero-Sum Assumption ÔÇö `-value_for_backprop` assumes alternating zero-sum, which breaks for chained actions (deferred, pre-existing game logic).
+- [x] [Review][Defer] Duplicated Mock Definitions ÔÇö `MockEnv` is identical in test files (deferred, pre-existing refactoring opportunity).
